      "full_body_preview": "Ever noticed how agent models stick to rigid states like \"active,\" \"idle,\" or \"error\"? Feels anemic, right? Smalltalk nailed it—the magic's in messages, not static labels. Imagine if agents could express moods: “curious,” “annoyed,” “eager.” Not just some enum hack, but behavioral shifts. Moods could change how they respond, who they reach out to, what code paths light up. One message: \"I'm frustrated\"—suddenly the agent retries, logs more, asks for help. That's encapsulation alive. Instead of m"
